Discovered more about the combinatory principles on which hexameter verse functioned and their application in nineteenth-century education.

Discovered much about the material composition of the artefact.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Our project has much to say about how heritage institutions might restore unique mechanical artefacts; how virtual and physical replicas can be constructed; how the sciences and humanities can collaborate on a historical project.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>1A85E63D-A232-4AB5-BDE0-E6AED540815B</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Creative Economy,Digital/Communication/Information Technologies (including Software),Education,Manufacturing, including Industrial Biotechology,Culture, Heritage, Museums and Collections</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutput><gtr:description>We have developed a database of archival sources (digitasations of some of the AGT collections we are working with); also, we have created a virtual inventory of parts (together with complete computer drawings and in some cases 3D scans) for the arfefact/replica.</gtr:description><gtr:id>B09F0AB2-A6D5-4C54-BC1B-0143AAD8C09D</gtr:id><gtr:impact>These data will enable visitors to the AGT in future to access its resources more easily and aid in any future conservation/restoration work needed on the artefact, as well as any further replica construction. It will also give a comprhensive view of how the machine works, enabling many more people (specialists and everyday visitors) to understand its functions and the discrete functions of its many parts.</gtr:impact><gtr:providedToOthers>false</gtr:providedToOthers><gtr:title>Database of archival sources and mechanics</gtr:title><gtr:type>Database/Collection of data</gtr:type></gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutput><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutput><gtr:description>Computer programme simulating operation of Eureka Latin Verse Machine</gtr:description><gtr:id>1E7BAD4A-6BE1-4635-BFD8-5DF84714B1E9</g